## Future Enhancement (Post-Production Validation)

Once CLI mode is proven in production, add recommendation:

```go
if isClaudeDetected() && !hasMCP && !hasHooks {
    fmt.Println("âš  Claude integration not set up")
    fmt.Println("  Run: bd setup claude")
    fmt.Println("  Tip: CLI mode (without MCP) uses fewer tokens than MCP server")
    fmt.Println("       Both approaches work equally well - choose based on preference")
}
```

This recommendation should only be added after CLI mode with `bd prime` is validated in real-world usage.

## Implementation

Add to tip registry in `cmd/bd/tips.go`:

```go
{
    ID: "claude_setup",
    Condition: func() bool {
        return isClaudeDetected() && !isClaudeSetupComplete()
    },
    Message: "Run 'bd setup claude' to enable automatic context recovery in Claude Code",
    Frequency: 24 * time.Hour,  // Daily minimum gap
    Priority: 100,              // Highest priority
    Probability: 0.6,           // 60% chance when eligible
}
```

## Detection Logic

```go
func isClaudeDetected() bool {
    // Check environment variables
    if os.Getenv("CLAUDE_CODE") != "" || os.Getenv("ANTHROPIC_CLI") != "" {
        return true
    }
    // Check if .claude/ directory exists
    if _, err := os.Stat(filepath.Join(os.Getenv("HOME"), ".claude")); err == nil {
        return true
    }
    return false
}

func isClaudeSetupComplete() bool {
    // Check for global installation
    home, err := os.UserHomeDir()
    if err == nil {
        _, err1 := os.Stat(filepath.Join(home, ".claude/commands/prime_beads.md"))
        _, err2 := os.Stat(filepath.Join(home, ".claude/hooks/sessionstart"))
        if err1 == nil && err2 == nil {
            return true  // Global hooks installed
        }
    }

    // Check for project installation
    _, err1 := os.Stat(".claude/commands/prime_beads.md")
    _, err2 := os.Stat(".claude/hooks/sessionstart")
    return err1 == nil && err2 == nil
}
```

## Priority and Probability Behavior

**Why 60% probability?**
- Important message (priority 100) but not critical
- Daily frequency + 60% = shows ~4 times per week
- Avoids spam while staying visible
- Balances persistence with user experience

**Comparison with other probabilities:**
- 100% probability: Shows EVERY day (annoying)
- 80% probability: Shows ~6 days per week (too frequent)
- 60% probability: Shows ~4 days per week (balanced)
- 40% probability: Shows ~3 days per week (might be missed)

**Auto-stops when setup complete:**
- Condition becomes false after `bd setup claude`
- No manual dismissal needed
- Tip naturally disappears from rotation
